# Unwash README
---

## Install requirements:
```
pip install -r unwashproject/requirements.txt
```


## Other dependencies:
Install GDAL from:
```
wget http://www.kyngchaos.com/files/software/frameworks/GDAL_Complete-1.11.dmg
```


## Get the postgis docker repo from:
```
git clonehttps://github.com/rca/docker-postgis
```


## Build it:
```
docker build -t gis .
```


## When using boot2docker, create a volume for the container:
```
boot2docker ssh 'sudo mkdir -p /srv/postgis/var/lib/postgresql'
```


## Fire up a container, note the host port is fixed to 15432:
```
GIS=$(docker run -d -p 15432:5432 -v /srv/postgis/var/lib/postgresql:/var/lib/postgresql -e USERNAME=docker -e PASS=docker gis)
```


Logging into the PostgreSQL instance (pass: docker):
```
psql -h 192.168.59.103 -p 15432 -U docker -W postgres;
CREATE EXTENSION postgis;
CREATE EXTENSION postgis_topology;
```


## In the project base directory, create a .env file to set the DATABASE_URL:
```
echo 'export DATABASE_URL=postgis://docker:docker@192.168.59.103:15432/unwash' >> .env
```

## Sync database:
```
python manage.py syncdb --noinput
```


## Migrate data:
```
python manage.py migrate
```


##Load up countries:
```
python manage.py oscar_populate_countries
```

Oscar sets the default store location to GB, the store locale must be changed within the DB to US
for the checkout process to work properly. (RCA has written a south migration to automate this change)

